summary: An email exchange between FBI personnel regarding scheduling a call with an Assistant United States Attorney (AUSA) about the Ghislaine Maxwell case. The email indicates the recipient has not been involved with the case.

events.description: An FBI agent is asked to schedule a call with an Assistant United States Attorney regarding the Ghislaine Maxwell case.

keyFacts: An FBI agent is being asked to schedule a call with a federal prosecutor (AUSA) about Ghislaine Maxwell in April 2021.
The email indicates the agent has 'not touched that case,' suggesting they were not previously involved in the Maxwell investigation.
The communication shows ongoing coordination between the FBI and the U.S. Attorney's Office regarding the Maxwell case.
